{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place parsley in mixing bowl and chop <nobr>3 sec\/speed 7<\/nobr>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside.","Place water in mixing bowl. Place cleaned mussels in Varoma dish, set Varoma in position and steam <nobr>15 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<\/nobr>. Remove Varoma and check that mussels have all opened. If not, remove open mussels and transfer to a bowl, set Varoma back in position and steam a further <nobr>5-10 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<\/nobr>. Remove Varoma, discard any mussels that remain closed, transfer open mussels to bowl and set aside. Strain cooking liquid through a fine mesh sieve into another bowl and set aside.","Place extra virgin olive oil, shallots, garlic and red chilli (if using) in mixing bowl and chop <nobr>7 sec\/speed 5<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Sauté <nobr>3 min\/120°C\/speed 1<\/nobr>.","Add white wine (if using) and cherry tomatoes and cook <nobr>2 min\/100°C\/speed 1<\/nobr>.","Add tomato purée and reserved cooking liquid, adding water to reach 700 g, then bring to a boil <nobr>7 min\/100°C\/speed 1<\/nobr>.","Add salt and penne and cook for <nobr>time indicated on packet\/100°C\/\/speed <\/nobr> or until al dente. Meanwhile, remove mussels from opened shells, reserving some in their shells to garnish and set aside.","Transfer pasta to a serving bowl, add shelled mussels, combine using spatula and drizzle with extra virgin olive oil. Garnish with reserved chopped parsley, reserved mussels in their shells and serve hot."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["4 - 5 sprigs fresh flat-leaf parsley, leaves only","250 g water","1000 g fresh mussels, scrubbed and debearded","30 g extra virgin olive oil","30 g shallots, halved","3 garlic cloves","1 fresh red chilli, small, deseeded (optional)","50 g dry white wine              (optional)","120 g cherry tomatoes, halved","40 - 50 g tomato purée","1 pinch salt","350 g penne or similar short dried pasta"]}],"id":"r150892","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-Ob9PLnHhSTA\/XZMzM5LAVSI\/AAAAAAAAauY\/CAz5v9nmCI0PQ6x3LWgS7uF3AQPfHXDYACLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_XnTOcBrqFfNk_WGt.png","title":"Penne with Mussels","publishedAt":"2017-06-01T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"17 g","fat":"15 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"65 g","calories":"2011 kJ \/ 480 kcal"},"usefulItems":"fine mesh sieve","hintsAndTricks":["<i>In this dish the cooking method is borrowed from risotto: the pasta absorbs the liquid released by the mussels and at the same time adds starch to the sauce for a creamy and mouth-watering result. Add a chilli for a little kick, if you  wish.<\/i>","Fresh mussels can be replaced with frozen mussels. In this case, they must be defrosted first."],"basicInfo":["easy","35m","2h 5m","4 portions"]}